    "Figure 8 show the correlation before and after normalization.",
    "Such relationships can be useful in understanding how the features relate to each other and how they may affect the target variable (the 'label' which indicates whether an instance is an attack or not).",
    "To check interactions of the features and their dependence on the binary labels we compute a correlation matrix.",
    "This matrix help to measure the linear regression between the features and the target variable or between two features.",
    "The Figure 9 shows a correlation matrix between Binary class labels is constructed, illustrated in the following table: This figure depicts the correlation matrix of features in the UNSW-NB15 dataset, highlighting their relationships with binary class labels (0: normal, 1: attack)."
